gurmukhi: ਜੋੳੂ ਅਾਨਿ ਮਿਲੇ ਨਹਿ ਜੋਰਿ ਲਰੇ ||
transliteration: Jooo Aan(i) Mile Nah(i) Jor(i) Dare||
translation: Those who did not surrender and fought violently,
Their bodies were bound and reduced to ashes in big fires.
They were burnt in the fire-altar-pit uninformed.
Thus there was a very great sacrifice of Kshatriyas.21.311.

gurmukhi: ੲਿਤਿ ਅਜੈ ਸਿੰਘ ਕਾ ਰਾਜ ਸੰਪੂਰਨ ਭੲਿਅਾ ||
transliteration: It(i) Ajai Singh Kaa Raaj Sanpooran Bhaiaa||
translation: Here ends the complete Description of the Rule of Ajai Singh.

gurmukhi: ਬਿਅਾਸੀ ਬਰਖ ਪਰਮਾਨ || ਦਿਨ ਦੋੲਿ ਮਾਸ ਅਸਟਾਨ ||
transliteration: Biaasibarakh Parmaan|| Deen Doe Maas Astaan||
translation: For eighty-two years, eight months and two days,

gurmukhi: ਬਹੁ ਰਾਜ ਭਾਗ ਕਮਾੲਿ || ਪੁਨਿ ਨ੍ਰਿਪ ਕੋ ਨ੍ਰਿਪਰਾੲਿ ||੧||੩੧੨||
transliteration: Bahu Raaj Bhaag Kamaae|| Poun(i) Nrip Ko Nripraae||1||312||
translation: Ruled very prosperously the king of kings (Ajai Singh).1.312.

gurmukhi: ਸੁਨ ਰਾਜ ਰਾਜ ਮਹਾਨ || ਦਸ ਚਾਰ ਚਾਰ ਨਿਧਾਨ ||
transliteration: Soun Raaj Raaj Mahaan|| Das Chaar Chaar Nidhaan||
translation: Listen, the king of great kingdom, who was treasure of fourteen learnings;

gurmukhi: ਦਸ ਦੋੲਿ ਦੁਅਾਦਸ ਮੰਤ || ਧਰਨੀ ਧਰਾਨ ਮਹੰਤ ||੨||੩੧੩||
transliteration: Das Doe Duaadas Mant|| Dharnidharaan Mahant||2||313||
translation: Who recited the mantra of twelve letters and was the Supreme Sovereign on the earth.2.313.

gurmukhi: ਪੁਨਿ ਭਯੋ ੳੁਦੋਤ ਨ੍ਰਿਪਾਲ || ਰਸ ਰੀਤਿ ਰੂਪ ਰਸਾਲ ||
transliteration: Poun(i) Bhayo Udot Nripaal|| Ras Reet(i) Roop Rasaal||
translation: Then the great king Jag took birth, who was very beautiful and affectionate;

gurmukhi: ਅਤਿ ਭਾਨ ਤੇਜ ਪ੍ਰਚੰਡ || ਅਨਖੰਡ ਤੇਜ ਪ੍ਰਚੰਡ ||੩||੩੧੪||
transliteration: At(i) Bhaan Tej Prachanndd|| Ankhanndtej Prachanndd||3||314||
translation: Who was highly lustrous than the sun, His great effulgence was indestructible.3.314.
